text: “The human body is an unusual sort of Instagram subject: it can be adjusted, with the right kind of effort, to perform better and better over time,” @jiatolentino writes. https://t.co/BdUobGaLoV

text: Poetry anthologies, with their diverse voices but convergent ideas, envision a public sphere in which solidarity doesn’t require uniformity, Clare Bucknell writes. https://t.co/SoxPfDT1mY
